<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-19T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-19T08:00:00-05:00" n="175" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d175">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002 Manchuria/206: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_GJC1" type="from">Grew</persName>) to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-19T22:00:00+09:00">July 19, 1932—10
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 19—10:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>191. Following from the Consul at Dairen.</p>
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“July 19, 2 p.m. All 10 Japanese customs officials and 54 clerks,
                                including 20 new ones, now operating Manchukuo customs in old
                                building. British Assistant Commissioner and 58 officials and clerks
                                of Maritime Customs, mostly Chinese, continue at desks in old
                                building. Kwantung Government allows new services to function and
                                has acted to prevent Maritime Customs from remitting million yen
                                collected before customs taken over. Full report follows.”<note n="5" xml:id="d175fn5">Not printed.</note></p>
                        </quote>
                        <p>Copy by mail to Peiping.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_GJC1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>